## Exp 05 Results Analysis

| Gene    | FNR  | PPV  | MCC  | FN p50 CRR | Diagnosis            |
|---------|------|------|------|------------|----------------------|
| CRT     | 0.04 | 1.00 | 0.98 | 1.50       | Near-perfect         |
| GCH1    | 0.29 | 0.95 | 0.80 | 1.18       | Weak signal + HMM    |
| MDR1    | 0.11 | 1.00 | 0.94 | 1.43       | HMM discarding signal|
| PM2_PM3 | 0.98 | 1.00 | 0.14 | 1.47       | HMM discarding signal — critical |

**Root cause:** PM2_PM3 is catastrophic (367 FN, 7 TP). FN p50 CRR=1.47 >> 1.0 confirms signal is present; `hmm_self_transition=0.75` makes it too costly for Viterbi to enter amplified states on 7-bin genes where signal is consistently elevated but not extreme. MDR1 AF-W (FNR=1.00) shows the same pattern.

**Fix:** Lower `hmm_self_transition` 0.75 → 0.65.

